    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ASN.1 encoding error causing malformed FAPI messages in nvIPC\n\n### Summary\nThe nvIPC interface was producing malformed FAPI protocol messages due to insufficient buffer sizes for ASN.1 encoding operations. This occurred because mempool sizes were only initialized conditionally based on a hardcoded CUDA device ID check that always evaluated to false.\n\nThe buffer sizes for CPU message and data pools were never properly set, resulting in default/zero sized buffers that caused buffer overflows during ASN.1 encoding.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/aerial/fapi_nvIPC.c`: Modified `load_hard_code_config` to always initialize mempool sizes regardless of CUDA device ID, ensuring sufficient buffer space for ASN.1 encoding of FAPI messages.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder load, the VNF would produce corrupted FAPI messages with invalid ASN.1 encoding that caused downstream parsing failures in the PNF. Messages would appear truncated or contain garbage data where valid protocol fields were expected.\n\nThe issue was observable through FAPI message tracing showing malformed message headers and incorrect length fields that exceeded available buffer space.\n"
}